<HEADLINE> Teen Said to Mix Sheep Eye in Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PAINESVILLE, Ohio (AP) -- A 16-year-old student faces expulsion  
for slicing up a sheep's eye during biology class and mixing it in 
rigatoni eaten by two classmates, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy, whose name was not released, admitted that he sliced up  
the eye at Riverside High School and put it in the food, said Lake 
County Sheriff's Lt. Lonnie Sparkman. 
</P>
<P>
	The two 17-year-old girls who ate the pasta on Monday didn't get  
sick, authorities said. The boy was suspended for 10 days, said 
school Principal Dennis Holmes. 
</P>
<P>
	He and his 17-year-old brother were later placed in a juvenile  
detention facility for threatening to duplicate the April 20 school 
shootings in Littleton, Colo., that left 15 people dead. 
</P>
<P>
	The brothers were charged with aggravated menacing and inducing  
panic, said William Crosier, a deputy sheriff. 
</P>
