<HEADLINE> Wild Event Wins Turf Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Wild Event passed Garbu in the final  
yards and scored a head victory in a three-horse photo in the 
$333,300 Early Times Turf Classic at Churchill Downs Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Seven weeks ago, Wild Event lost to Garbu as the favorite at  
Gulfstream Park. This time, Garbu caught Aboriginal Apex at the top 
of the stretch and opened a length lead, but Wild Event, under 
Shane Sellers, began to slowly cut into the margin. 
</P>
<P>
	As the fourth choice in the field of seven, Wild Event returned  
$13.20, $5.40 and $3.20. Garbu paid $4.40 and $3, and finished a 
nose in front of Hawkskley Hill, the favorite, who returned $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Trained by Lou Goldfine, the winner covered the 1 1/8 miles in 1:47  
1-5 in the Grade I event and earned $206,646 for Arthur Appleton. 
</P>
<P>
	Garbu had won two straight since trainer Bill Mott added the  
anti-bleeder medication Lasix. 
</P>
<P>
	More Than Ready was just that in the $120,400 WHAS Stakes for  
2-year-olds. The colt took the lead turning into the stretch and 
pulled away for a 4 1/2-length victory over House Burner. 
</P>
<P>
	More Than Ready is trained by Todd Pletcher, who has a  
reputation for outstanding results with 2-year-olds in their second 
race. More Than Ready's first start was a 7 1/2-length victory at 
Keeneland three weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
	As the second choice in the field of 12, More Than Ready paid  
$9.40, $5.80 and $4.00. Patrick Byrne, who won the WHAS in 1997 
with Favorite Trick, trained House Burner and the show horse, 
favored Admiral Perry. 
</P>
<P>
	House Burner paid $10.20 and $6.20. It was another half-length  
back to Admiral Perry, who paid $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
	James T. Scatuorchio paid $187,000 for More Than Ready as a  
yearling and got back $74,648 in purse money Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by John Velazquez, More Than Ready was fifth around the  
turn. Velazquez kept Pat Day and House Burner inside and behind the 
leaders turning into the stretch. After four whacks with the whip, 
More Than Ready had opened a comfortable advantage. 
</P>
<P>
	In other stakes races on Derby Day:  
</P>
<P>
	--Rock and Roll held off Liberty Gold by a half-length in the  
$166,350 Churchill Downs Handicap. Ridden by Pat Day, Rock and Roll 
paid $15 after covering the seven furlongs in 1:22 4-5. Fourth into 
the turn, Rock and Roll caught Orville n Wilbur's inside the final 
eighth. 
</P>
<P>
	--Next to last turning into the stretch, Shires Ende moved to the  
middle of the track and ran past seven opponents to score a 
two-length victory in the $119,600 Ashland Mile. Ridden by 
Velazquez, Shires Ende paid $80.20 after covering a mile on the 
grass in 1:35 2-5. 
</P>
<P>
	--Sellers got Zuppardo Ardo off the rail in the final 100 yards  
and caught a tiring Prospector's Song for a half-length victory in 
the Humana Distaff Handicap. Last early in the field of nine, 
Zuppardo Ardo paid $10.60 after running the seven furlongs in 1:23 
2-5. French Braids nipped Prospector's Song by a nose for second. 
</P>
