<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Two Convicted in Gang Rape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Two men have been convicted of leading the gang  
rape of a woman assaulted at a public housing project over a 
two-hour period while up to 60 people gathered to watch. 
</P>
<P>
	Larry Brown and Kahbarious Jackson, both 18, were found guilty  
Friday of several charges, including rape and aggravated sodomy. 
They face up to life in prison at their sentencing June 4. 
</P>
<P>
	The 28-year-old victim was seeking crack cocaine when she went  
to the south Fulton County housing complex Aug. 15 to make a buy, 
attorneys said. She was dumped by a nervous cab driver. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown and Jackson grabbed the woman, seeking either $10 or the  
cocaine they claimed Brown had given her. She had neither, so the 
two decided to call in the debt in sex -- a rape in the courtyard of 
the complex. 
</P>
<P>
	It went on for two hours, witnesses said, and did not stop until  
a woman stopped Brown as he was about to dump a bucket of water on 
the semiconscious victim. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorneys said the woman had offered sex for the drugs  
and the exchange had gotten out of hand. Prosecutor Ingrid Skidmore 
scoffed at that notion. 
</P>
<P>
	``If that's the case, then what happened to the drugs? She  
should have left with a bag full,'' Ms. Skidmore said. 
</P>
<P>
	Two other men were tried in the case. One was acquitted of all  
charges, and another was found guilty of sodomy. Charges against 
five others were dropped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990501.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-01 00:52:25 </DATE_TIME>
