<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clash 2, Burn 1, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Ronald Cerritos scored in regulation and  
Dario Brose won the game with a rare shootout penalty kick to lead 
the San Jose Clash over the Dallas Burn 2-1 Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Brose got the penalty kick in the fifth round to clinch the  
victory for the Clash (5-2). 
</P>
<P>
	He overran the ball during his shootout attempt, giving  
goalkeeper Matt Jordan time to reach the edge of the penalty area 
before Brose could attempt a shot. 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan was judged to have handled Brose's shot outside the area.  
The goalkeeper was ejected and San Jose was awarded the penalty 
kick. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose played almost the entire game a man short. Defender  
John Doyle was ejected in the seventh minute for a two-footed 
tackle on midfielder Ted Eck. 
</P>
<P>
	Temoc Suarez put Dallas (4-3) ahead in the sixth minute, but  
Cerritos tied the score in the 13th minute with an 11-yard shot 
after Jeff Baicher stole a pass by Eric Dade. 
</P>
<P>
	Dade later left with a broken cheekbone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
