<HEADLINE> Bucks Activate Sam Cassell </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Milwaukee Bucks activated guard Sam Cassell  
prior to Saturday night's game against the Boston Celtics and 
placed guard Dell Curry on the injured list with lower back spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	Cassell was placed on the injured list on March 22 with a  
sprained right ankle. He originally injured the ankle earlier this 
season while he was with the New Jersey Nets. 
</P>
<P>
	After joining the Bucks in a three-team trade on March 11,  
Cassell re-injured the ankle in his Bucks' debut against the 
Charlotte Hornets on March 21. 
</P>
<P>
	Cassell has played in just five games this season -- one for the  
Bucks -- and is averaging 17 points, 4.6 assists and 1.4 rebounds in 
25.2 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Curry, who played in the first half Friday night against  
Detroit, sat out the second half because of the back spasms and 
didn't make the trip to Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	In 42 games this season, Curry was averaging 10.1 points and 2.0  
rebounds. 
</P>
