<HEADLINE> Glider Crash Kills 3 in Pa. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HILLTOWN, Pa. (AP) -- A small plane and a glider collided  
Saturday, killing the pilot of the airplane and two men in the 
glider, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	No one on the ground was injured, though the glider crashed in a  
nearby back yard next to a crowded athletic field in Bucks County 
about 30 miles north of Philadelphia, said Township Deputy Fire 
Chief Shawn Shade. 
</P>
<P>
	Debris from the plane landed in front of a home.  
</P>
<P>
	The single-engine Cessna had been towing another glider, whose  
pilot saw the second glider approaching and dropped his tow in time 
to avoid the collision, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The pilot of the first glider returned safely to the nearby  
Philadelphia Glider Club airfield, said Township Police Chief Kerry 
Trauger. The crash site was about a mile from the club. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no immediate indication how high the plane and the  
glider were when they collided. 
</P>
