<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The Carolinas and northern Georgia received showers Saturday,  
with fair skies in the nation's mid-section and mild conditions in 
the East. 
</P>
<P>
	A potent area of high pressure continued to bring fair weather  
to much of the Midwest. Showers dampened the central and southern 
Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	In the West, a storm system was centered in the southern  
Rockies, producing rain and snow from Wyoming south through western 
Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Higher elevations of Colorado continued to receive light snow  
with rain in lower elevations, prompting flood watches and warnings 
across the region. Conditions were fair and dry along the West 
Coast with showers in Washington and Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the lower 48 states was 77 degrees in  
McAllen, Texas. The low was 23 degress in Leadville, Colo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
