<HEADLINE> Mutiny 2, Fusion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Musa Shannon scored in his fifth consecutive  
game and Carlos Valderrama had an assist against his former team as 
the Tampa Bay Mutiny beat the Miami Fusion 2-1 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Valderrama, who played for the Mutiny in 1996 and 1997, saw his  
night end early when referee Alex Prus issued a red card after the 
midfielder's slide tackle from behind on Henry Gutierrez. 
</P>
<P>
	Shannon opened the scoring in the sixth minute and Valderrama  
set up Jefferson Gottardi's goal that made it 2-0 in the 28th 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Diego Serna scored the Miami goal on a header in the 69th  
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	The assist for Valderrama, who received a standing ovation  
during pregame introductions in his Mutiny home debut this season, 
was his first since the Colombian standout was reassigned from 
Miami to Tampa Bay by MLS commissioner Doug Logan on April 23. 
</P>
<P>
	The league action stemmed from a severely strained relationship  
between Valderrama and Fusion coach Ivo Wortmann that eventually 
found the midfielder being benched. 
</P>
<P>
	After starting the season with four losses, Tampa Bay has won  
two straight with Valderrama in the lineup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
