<HEADLINE> Lee Leaves Motley Crue for Family </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Tommy Lee is getting another divorce, this  
time from Motley Crue. 
</P>
<P>
	The 37-year-old drummer said he's leaving the rock group he  
founded in 1981 with Nikki Sixx and will not be joining them on 
this summer's ``Maximum Rock'' tour. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will miss them and the fans, but it's time for me to totally  
embrace my family and my new projects,'' Lee said Thursday, the 
same day he and wife Pamela Anderson Lee said they had reconciled. 
</P>
<P>
	Guns 'N Roses drummer Matt Sorum was asked to replace Lee for  
the 40-city summer tour beginning in late June. Band spokeswoman 
Ashley Smith said Friday that Sorum has yet to accept. 
</P>
<P>
	Lee and his wife, the star of TV's ``V.I.P'' and a former  
``Baywatch'' actress, said they have decided to reunite and rebuild 
their family a year after their divorce. Lee was arrested for 
hitting her while on probation for attacking a photographer. He was 
given three years of probation and ordered to stay 100 yards away 
from Ms. Anderson. 
</P>
<P>
	Now they're living together in Malibu. They have two children,  
3-year-old Brandon and 1-year-old Dylan. 
</P>
